{
  "aspect": "vertical", "theme": "navy", "fps": 30, "crossfade": 0.6, "pace": 1.4,
  "voiceover": "Where is God when it hurts? This is less an argument to win than a wound to sit with — so let me be gentle. Christianity's distinct answer to pain isn't a clever explanation. It's a God who didn't stay at a safe distance from it. In Jesus, God entered the world of grief, betrayal, torture, and death himself. So whatever you're facing, you're not facing it watched by a stranger. Scripture says 'the Lord is close to the brokenhearted' — Psalm 34:18 — and that nothing, not trouble or anguish, can separate you from his love — Romans 8:38-39. And doubt and lament are not faithlessness; the Bible is full of both. If you're in a dark place right now, that's exactly where this God has promised to meet people. You're not alone. He came in.",
